         <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng" resp="part:jeth">
 	       <p>
 	         <!-- The translation is preliminary -->
 	         A field given by the first, dear son of the Adhirāja of the great Bāṇas, (Śrī Bhūpala(?))-Vikramāditya <!-- the simple reference to Vikramāditya indicates that it was Vikramāditya I --> of which the witness(es are): Puṟanullu Salkiraṭṭakuḍi, [...] (are the) witness(es).
 	         <!-- It probably has to be read tāyu (for dāyu) in line 19: "those who come and impede...". As for pondu conf. SII X, 651, line 17-18: "has killed [...] and will get (the punishment of that)".
 	         In line 24 it has to be read ḻacci<na>. Lines 22-23 perhaps have to be read as dēvadrō|ṇuḷu; ⟨ṇu⟩ and ⟨gu⟩ can be similar enough to be confused. -->
 	       </p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>
              Line 10 of this edition is numbered 9a by N. Lakshminarayan Rao and was omitted by J. Ramayya Pantulu. Hence, line 11 corresponds to line 10 in both editions etc.
            </p>
         </div>
        <div type="bibliography">
          <p>
            The inscription was noted in A. R. No. 403 of 1904 <!-- has to be adjusted to the @target --> and first published by J. Ramayya Pantulu (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:RamayyaPantulu1948_01"/><citedRange unit="page">336</citedRange><citedRange unit="item">617</citedRange></bibl>). His reading was improved by N. Lakshminarayan Rao (<bibl rend="omitname"><ptr target="bib:LakshminarayanRao1948_02"/><citedRange unit="page">lvii-lviii</citedRange></bibl>). K. M. Sastri reprints the unimproved reading and provides a summary: <cit><quote>Refers to a gift of land by the eldest dear son of Vikramāditya and contains an imprecation.</quote><bibl><ptr target="bib:Sastri1969_01"/><citedRange unit="page">336</citedRange></bibl></cit>.   
          </p>
